FBIS3-12965 "drnes045_k_94008" FBIS-NES-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 IRAQ Memo to UN Protests Recent U.S. Air Activity JN0603133494 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1130 GMT 6 Mar 94 JN0603133494 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Iraq has lodged a fresh protest with the United Nations against Iraqi airspace violations by U.S. aircraft for purposes of surveillance and harassment, and to drop flares. A protest memorandum delivered to the UN secretary general by the Iraqi permanent representative to the United Nations yesterday stated that U.S. aircraft conducted 421 air sorties over Iraqi territory during period 21-28 February. U.S. aircraft flew at medium altitudes over areas in northern and southern Iraq, including Mosul, Irbil, Dahuk, Zakho, al-Nasiriyah, al-Samawah, al-'Amarah, al-Basrah, Artawi, al-Diwaniyah, Qal'at Salih, and al-Qusayr. The memorandum noted that a hostile plane dropped three flares over al-Shaykhan District in Ninawa Governorate on 24 February. On 26 February, TR-1 U.S. reconnaissance aircraft violated Iraqi airspace over al-Samawah, al-'Amarah, southern al-Diwaniyah, al-Qurnah, and al-Basrah. Then, they headed for Saudi Arabia. Iraq requested that this memorandum be circulated as a UN Security Council document.
